We work hard to bring you unique gifts that last. It’s the people in small towns like ours who create a sense of community, pride and products worth being proud of. Like most small companies, we started small. In 1998, Gene and Kathie Schobinger entertained a wild idea to create weathervanes. As a result, we grew up cutting metal and packing boxes. Kim and Robert didn’t make the first weathervane, but we’ve perfected it. We did our research, we listened to our customers and we put in the work. We are a small company from a small community, so we value every customer as if they are part of our family. We pride ourselves on our hand-made unique products.
